 :tx/rationale "Create task: EPIC: Multi-Signal k_eff Estimation — self-calibrating Bayesian estimator (INV-REFLEXIVE-002). BACKGROUND: k_eff estimation currently uses a single proxy (total_turns from telemetry). This is inaccurate: at 15k datoms the proxy gives k*=0.15 even at session START. The real k_eff has MULTIPLE observable correlates: tx_count, wall_elapsed, tx_velocity, cumulative_output_tokens, observe_count. ROOT CAUSE: Latent variable inference with a single noisy feature. SOLUTION: Multi-signal fusion: k̂_eff = 1.0 - Σ(wᵢ × sigmoid(eᵢ/τᵢ)), where weights wᵢ and thresholds τᵢ are calibrated from the store's own session history. When --context-used is provided, record (evidence_vector, actual_k) as calibration datum. Over sessions, the estimator improves autonomously — C7 self-bootstrap applied to the observation apparatus. TRACES TO: INV-BUDGET-004, ADR-BUDGET-002, INV-HARVEST-005. ACCEPTANCE: |k̂_eff - k_true| ≤ 0.15 for sessions where --context-used is provided."
